00:12:58,003 --> 00:13:01,906
dialogue in addition to the tools we develop to organize and implement the stuff that we're

239
00:13:01,926 --> 00:13:02,246
going to make.

240
00:13:03,447 --> 00:13:05,648
Because one of the things I personally remember

241
00:13:06,189 --> 00:13:08,710
when I'm either at any stage of development

242
00:13:09,510 --> 00:13:11,872
is that nobody really cares about writing,

243
00:13:12,152 --> 00:13:13,032
like in the traditional sense.

244
00:13:13,733 --> 00:13:16,774
People just don't recognize objectively strong dialogue

245
00:13:17,295 --> 00:13:18,836
if it's presented to them statically,

246
00:13:19,016 --> 00:13:20,356
or in a laborious cut scene,

247
00:13:20,757 --> 00:13:22,437
or in a really obviously linear way.

248
00:13:23,518 --> 00:13:25,239
But if you let the player make a choice

249
00:13:25,539 --> 00:13:27,320
to deliver a particularly well-written line,

250
00:13:27,980 --> 00:13:29,601
then we're often told the writing's really good.

251
00:13:31,391 --> 00:13:33,052
That line, the exact same line,

252
00:13:33,492 --> 00:13:36,793
tucked into like an expertly crafted 90 second cutscene,

253
00:13:37,173 --> 00:13:38,894
gets completely dismissed if it's ever seen at all,

254
00:13:39,214 --> 00:13:41,095
because the player just feels like they're not moving forward.

255
00:13:45,057 --> 00:13:45,677
So, um...

256
00:13:46,838 --> 00:13:49,499
It's the writing's job to either not infringe on gameplay or actually be gameplay.

257
00:13:49,679 --> 00:13:51,059
This is one of the first things we prototyped.

258
00:13:51,540 --> 00:13:54,861
Check out that exclusive reveal of garbage!

259
00:13:54,881 --> 00:13:55,401
But, uh...

260
00:13:57,838 --> 00:14:00,299
Because the game we're working on is in first person, and it's an ideal world.

261
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:02,180
We'd absolutely never take control away from the player.

262
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:04,401
We need tools, and again these principles,

263
00:14:05,361 --> 00:14:07,482
to interrupt dialogue in a realistic way.

264
00:14:07,502 --> 00:14:10,543
Because you can walk around with this thing that makes people talk.

